## Why Preview Has Felt Problematic (And How To Stabilize It)

Given the current setup, preview issues are usually one of these:
- Sandpack iframe/runtime limitations for non-React or multi-service app flows
- Missing bridge from editor files to your actual project build/runtime
- Port and host mismatch when trying to treat this like a real app server preview
- "Looks like IDE" but still running demo files in memory, causing expectation mismatch

Hardening actions:
- Keep Sandpack for quick demo/runtime mode
- Add a second preview adapter for real project preview (served app or worker route)
- Add explicit mode indicator: `Demo Runtime` vs `Project Runtime`
- Add preview error surface in UI (instead of silent failure)

## Cohesion Plan for the Main Project

Use this folder as a "workbench engine" and wire it into the rest of SuperIDE in phases.

### Phase 1: Product Integration (fast win)
- Mount this workbench as a first-class route in your main app shell
- Reuse existing auth/session so IDE inherits user/org context
- Keep current Sandpack demo mode for reliability while backend endpoints are added

### Phase 2: Real File System Wiring
- Replace `defaultFiles` with file provider calls
- Add file tree hydration + lazy file content loading
- Add save actions with optimistic UI and dirty markers

Suggested contract:
- `GET /api/ide/tree`
- `GET /api/ide/file?path=...`
- `PUT /api/ide/file?path=...`
- `POST /api/ide/files/batch-save`

### Phase 3: Run/Preview Cohesion
- Keep current Sandpack preview as `Quick Preview`
- Add `Project Preview` lane backed by your real runtime (worker/server)
- Add runtime selector in topbar/statusbar

### Phase 4: Git + Diagnostics Cohesion
- Wire activity rail `git` button to real branch/status/diff panel
- Wire lint/test errors to an IDE diagnostics panel
- Connect smoke scripts/artifacts as a "release readiness" panel

### Phase 5: Team Workflow Upgrades
- Command palette
- Shared workspace presets
- Session restore (open files, cursor locations, panel layout)
- Workspace-level notifications for pipeline/build states

